  <description><![CDATA[<p>VOI Alimini Resort is a great family-friendly property on the shores of Southern <a data-udi="umb://document/d0c28188245b40a396dd64fb346dffcd" href="/{localLink:umb://document/d0c28188245b40a396dd64fb346dffcd}" title="Puglia &amp; Basilicata">Puglia</a>. With 308 rooms spread over large grounds and countless facilities, couples and families of all ages are sure to have a great time away here.</p>
<p>The three-star hotel has comfortable and spacious rooms as well as three restaurants serving delicious Apulian cuisine, plus one exclusively for children. A large freshwater pool has plenty of sun beds on which to relax and the wide sandy beach is just a short walk away through the hotel grounds. Its gently sloping sands and clear waters make it a popular choice for those with younger children.</p>
<p>If you like to keep active, you’ll be spoilt for choice here with sports ranging from golf to football and tennis. There’s a spa for when you’d like to relax and in the evenings there’s entertainment for the whole family with professional shows. Children are well catered for with kids’ club for up to 17 years.</p>
<p>The hotel’s location makes it easy to explore the lovely coastal towns in <a data-udi="umb://document/3e930c14f9c54b6e9b4e0c6354960c61" href="/{localLink:umb://document/3e930c14f9c54b6e9b4e0c6354960c61}" title="Salento"><em>Salento</em></a>. Otranto is about 20 minutes away by can and the stunning baroque town of <em>Lecce</em> is around a 45-minute drive away.</p>]]></description>
