  <facilityDescription><![CDATA[<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Restaurants &amp; Bars</strong></span></p>
<p><strong>Central Restaurant</strong> is conveniently located in the resort with a lovely terrace overlooking the pool. It offers typical Apulian cuisine in and guests can eat dinner here as part of the half board package.</p>
<p><strong>Beach Restaurant</strong> is positioned directly on the beach and offers a rich buffet of barbecued meat, fish and pizza. Special menus for children are available.</p>
<p><strong>Osteria Salentina</strong> is open for dinner and serves specialities from the Salento region. Children’s menus are available here.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Pools &amp; Beaches</strong></span></p>
<p>There’s a large freshwater pool at the hotel with plenty of sun loungers and umbrellas for guests. A short walk through the hotel’s grounds will take you to the stunning sandy beach. It’s gently sloping banks make it great for families.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Spa</strong></span></p>
<p>A wellness centre is available for a charge and has a Jacuzzi, relaxation area, sauna and treatments.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Activities</strong></span></p>
<p>There’s plenty to keep you active at this resort with two football pitches (one 5-a-side), golf pitch &amp; putt, beach volley court, tennis courts, table tennis, bowls and a fitness room with a weights area.</p>]]></facilityDescription>
  <familyDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Voila Baby Club</strong> is a dedicated club for babies aged up to two years. It has all you need for your baby with bottle warmers, blenders, microwaves and fridges. You’re also able to reserve a baby kit for your arrival which has a stroller, high chair, baby bath and potty.</p>
<p><strong>Voila Kids</strong> has clubs for ages 3-6 yeas, 7-9 years and 10-12 years and included lunch and dinner. There are plenty of activities to enjoy like nature experiences, a kite lab and sport tournaments.</p>
<p><strong>Young Club</strong> caters for teenagers from 13-17 years and organises activities such as being an entertainer for a day, digital photo lab and drone experience. They’ll also be able to do watersports and enjoy video games in a dedicated area.</p>]]></familyDescription>
